# 🔐 GenAI-Based Manual Penetration Testing Automation

## 🧩 Problem Statement
Manual penetration testing (PT) was highly time-consuming, inconsistent, and dependent on individual expertise.  
Security validation often happened late in the SDLC, increasing release risk and delaying deployments.

---

## 🎯 Objective
- Automate manual penetration testing processes  
- Shift security validation earlier in SDLC (Shift-Left)  
- Improve test coverage and reduce release risks  

---

## 💡 Solution
Designed and delivered a **GenAI-powered penetration testing automation system** that leverages AI to generate test cases aligned with ASVS security standards.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview
- **Frontend:** Angular-based UI for test execution and reporting  
- **Backend:** .NET Core APIs handling orchestration  
- **AI Layer:** Azure OpenAI (GPT-based models)  
- **Automation:** Python + Selenium for test execution  
- **Data Layer:** SQL Server for logs and audit tracking  

---

## ⚙️ Key Features
-  AI-generated penetration testing scenarios  
-  Automated mapping of ASVS controls to test cases  
-  Auto-generation of Selenium test scripts  
-  Real-time execution logs and reporting  
-  Built-in compliance and audit traceability  

---

## 🧠 TPM Contributions
- Defined **AI security roadmap** and execution strategy  
- Led cross-functional teams (AI/ML, DevSecOps, QA)  
- Managed backlog, sprint planning, and stakeholder alignment  
- Established **Responsible AI governance framework**  

---

## 📈 Impact
-  Reduced penetration testing cycle time significantly  
-  Lowered release risk through early-stage validation  
-  Improved consistency and coverage of security testing  
-  Accelerated delivery timelines  

---

## 🔐 Governance & Compliance
- Human-in-the-loop validation for AI outputs  
- Full audit trail (EMP ID tracking, logs, RFC evidence)  
- Compliance with enterprise security and Responsible AI policies  

---

## 🧩 Key Learnings
- AI can drastically reduce manual effort in cybersecurity workflows  
- Governance and explainability are critical in AI-driven systems  
- Early security integration improves product quality and delivery speed  
